The paper deals with the problem of actively learning a linear classifier through query synthesis, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also discusses the curse of dimensionality, which is a well-known problem in computer science and statistics. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves computational complexity and theoretical analysis, which are relevant to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
